cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper proposes a new optimization algorithm that utilizes deep learning techniques, specifically model-driven deep learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of Markov decision processes, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance on benchmark functions, which falls under the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
